NGODWANA – Five people were injured after a truck veered off the Kaapsehoop Road.  According to ER24 branch manager, Greg Wilcox, the driver lost control of the truck and it veered across the N4 into a park area where it struck five men. “Four of the men had sustained moderate injuries, and the fifth sustained only minor injuries.” ALSO READ: Three major car accidents claim a total of 11 lives